radiographic_examinations.findings: There is bibasilar atelectasis. Equivocal subtle fat stranding in the region of the proximal sigmoid colon raises question of mild sigmoid diverticulitis. Bilateral subcentimeter renal hypodensities most likely represent simple cysts. No focal lesions in liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands. Normal kidneys, gallbladder, and small bowel. Enlarged prostate.
